dismissalText.commentary: Tanzid Hasan c Williamson b Bracewell 24 (24b 1x4 2x6 38m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: gottim, chipped to midwicket! "Beast" mode does it for NZ. Tossed up and Tanzid looks to launch into a heave across the line. Doesn't get the connection and Williamson snaps up a diving catch to his left. Bracewell strikes second ball and the Bangladesh opening stand comes to an abrupt end

image.longCaption: Will O'Rourke, player portrait, New Zealand vs South Africa, 2nd Test, Hamilton, 1st day, February 13, 2024

dismissalText.commentary: Najmul Hossain Shanto c Bracewell b O'Rourke 77 (110b 9x4 0x6 153m) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: top-edged up the chimney... and taken! There were several candidates to go for the catch, in the end Bracewell charged across from midwicket and pouched it safely diving forwards. Not sure mid-on or mid-off would have got there. O'Rourke watched it go, too, happy to take the notch in the wickets column. Shanto played well but falls at an inopportune moment

dismissalText.commentary: Towhid Hridoy c Williamson b Bracewell 7 (24b 0x4 0x6 33m) SR: 29.16

dismissalComment.html: pressure will do that to ya! Bracewell with a full ball outside off. Hridoy backs away and then tries to go over cover. But he slices it and the ball goes in the air. Williamson at cover spots it, turns around, runs back, and takes a catch from over his shoulder! Hridoy can't repeat his Dubai heroics

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Ravindra b Bracewell 2 (5b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: well, well, Bracewell! After a first-ball duck against India, Mushfiqur Rahim - Bangladesh's most experienced - tries to slog sweep the offspinner, and ends up holing out at deep midwicket. Tossed up around off. Mushfiqur gets down on one knee, but the bat swing isn't a 100%. Rachin makes no mistake in the deep

image.caption: Will O'Rourke, player portrait
image.longCaption: Will O'Rourke, player portrait, New Zealand vs South Africa, 2nd Test, Hamilton, 1st day, February 13, 2024

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c O'Rourke b Bracewell 4 (14b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: another wicket thrown away! And Bracewell has four! He bowls a flat-ish length ball on off. Mahmudullah comes down the wicket and tries to go for a big shot down the ground. But the length is just not there, and his wild swing of the bat gets a leading edge to the off side instead. O' Rourke at short third runs to his right and takes a tricky catch on the edge of the circle

dismissalText.commentary: Jaker Ali run out (†Latham) 45 (55b 3x4 1x6 94m) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: Jaker is run out trying to steal a bye to the keeper! Wide line, pace off, Taskin swung and missed. Jaker knew he wanted to be at the striker's end but is left well short by Latham's smart underarm into the stumps. He looks distraught as he picks himself up from the turf. A battling knock, but he won't finish the innings off

dismissalText.commentary: Rishad Hossain c Santner b Henry 26 (25b 2x4 1x6 23m) SR: 104

dismissalComment.html: swiped without timing to mid-off! Henry sticks with the short stuff and breaks the stand. Back of a length and rising outside off as Rishad tries to muscle it down the ground - but the shot didn't have the legs and it ends up being a simple catch for Santner going to his left

dismissalComment.html: pressure will do that to ya! Bracewell with a full ball outside off. Hridoy backs away and then tries to go over cover. But he slices it and the ball goes in the air. Williamson at cover spots it, turns around, runs back, and takes a catch from over his shoulder! Hridoy can't repeat his Dubai heroics

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Ravindra b Bracewell 2 (5b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: well, well, Bracewell! After a first-ball duck against India, Mushfiqur Rahim - Bangladesh's most experienced - tries to slog sweep the offspinner, and ends up holing out at deep midwicket. Tossed up around off. Mushfiqur gets down on one knee, but the bat swing isn't a 100%. Rachin makes no mistake in the deep

image.caption: Will O'Rourke, player portrait
image.longCaption: Will O'Rourke, player portrait, New Zealand vs South Africa, 2nd Test, Hamilton, 1st day, February 13, 2024

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c O'Rourke b Bracewell 4 (14b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: another wicket thrown away! And Bracewell has four! He bowls a flat-ish length ball on off. Mahmudullah comes down the wicket and tries to go for a big shot down the ground. But the length is just not there, and his wild swing of the bat gets a leading edge to the off side instead. O' Rourke at short third runs to his right and takes a tricky catch on the edge of the circle

dismissalText.commentary: Najmul Hossain Shanto c Bracewell b O'Rourke 77 (110b 9x4 0x6 153m) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: top-edged up the chimney... and taken! There were several candidates to go for the catch, in the end Bracewell charged across from midwicket and pouched it safely diving forwards. Not sure mid-on or mid-off would have got there. O'Rourke watched it go, too, happy to take the notch in the wickets column. Shanto played well but falls at an inopportune moment

dismissalText.commentary: Rishad Hossain c Santner b Henry 26 (25b 2x4 1x6 23m) SR: 104

dismissalComment.html: swiped without timing to mid-off! Henry sticks with the short stuff and breaks the stand. Back of a length and rising outside off as Rishad tries to muscle it down the ground - but the shot didn't have the legs and it ends up being a simple catch for Santner going to his left

dismissalText.commentary: Jaker Ali run out (†Latham) 45 (55b 3x4 1x6 94m) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: Jaker is run out trying to steal a bye to the keeper! Wide line, pace off, Taskin swung and missed. Jaker knew he wanted to be at the striker's end but is left well short by Latham's smart underarm into the stumps. He looks distraught as he picks himself up from the turf. A battling knock, but he won't finish the innings off

dismissalText.commentary: Will Young b Taskin Ahmed 0 (6b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: it's not a maiden over, no no, it's a wicket maiden! What a stunning delivery! Pitched up full just outside off. Young presses forward trying to defend down the ball's line. But the ball nips in after pitching, goes through the small gap between bat and pad, and the poles are scrambled.

dismissalText.commentary: Devon Conway b Mustafizur Rahman 30 (45b 6x4 0x6 69m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: a familiar form of dismissal for Conway, chopped on! His issue with the inside edge of his bat continues. Full ball just outside off. dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Nahid Rana 5 (4b 1x4 0x6 11m) SR: 125

dismissalComment.html: Nahid gets the edge!!!! And this 145kph+ ball is too good for KW. Fullish ball, sixth-stump line. Bit of movement away after pitching and Williamson drives away from his body with zero footwork. Takes the outside edge and Mushfiqur isn't dropping this. Williamson shakes his head on the walk back, making only 5 tonight. Another failure for him in this CT 2025 event
